[Post] job title

Feature: Happy case
Scenario: #CR-JOB1 - Create job title successfully without specification file
  Given user have a valid request body with title, description and note
  When user send POST request to /jobTitle API with: title: test123, description: description123, jobSpecification: null, note: note 123,
  Then the response status should be 200
  And the response should contain job title id
  And the title should be "test123"
  And the description should be "description123"
  And the note should be "note 123"
  And jobSpecification should be null
  And the response should match JSON schema:
{
  "data": {
	"id": number,
	"title": string,
	"description": string,
	"note": string,
	"jobSpecification": {
		"id": number | null,
		"filename": string | null,
		"fileType": string | null,
		"fileSize": string | null }
	},
	"meta": [],
	"rels": []
}

Scenario: #CR-JOB2 - Create job title with specification file
  Given user have a valid request body with title, description and note
  And user attach a valid specification file
  When user send POST request to /jobTitle API with: title: test123, description: description123, jobSpecification: null, note: note 123,
  Then the response status should be 200
  And jobSpecification id should not be null
  And filename should match uploaded file
  And fileType should be correct
  And fileSize should be greater than 0

Scenario: #CR-JOB3 - Create job title successfully with only title
  Given user have a valid request body with title
  When user send POST request to /jobTitle API with: title: valid title only, description: "", jobSpecification: null, note: "",
  Then the response status should be 200
  And the response should contain job title id
  And the title should be "valid title only"
  And the description should be empty
  And the note should be empty
  And jobSpecification should be null


